Russian Equity Movers: Lukoil, Mail.ru, Pharmstandard Are Active

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-08-31T11:08:15Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-31/russian-equity-movers-lukoil-mail-ru-pharmstandard-are-active.html
The 30-stock  Micex Index (INDEXCF)  rose for a
fourth day, increasing 1.2 percent to 1,531.5 by 2:12 p.m. in
Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index advanced 0.9 percent to
1,677.5 rubles.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO Lukoil (LKOH RX),  Russia ’s second-largest oil producer
headed for its highest close in four weeks after it said profit
increased 67 percent in the second quarter as crude prices
climbed, outweighing a decline in output. The shares increased 1
percent to 1,743.8 rubles, poised for their best close since
Aug. 3.  Mail.ru Group Ltd. (MAIL)   headed for its highest level
in almost four weeks after the Russian Facebook Inc. investor’s
first half-half earnings beat analysts’ expectations. The shares
advanced 7.1 percent in  London  to $34. A close at that level
would be its strongest since Aug. 4.  OAO  Pharmstandard (PHST)   rallied for a third day after
the Russian drugmaker said first-half profit gained 52 percent
on the year to 4.19 billion rubles ($145 million). The shares
rose as much as 6 percent and last traded 1.2 percent higher at
2,099.3 rubles.  To contact the reporter on this story:
